{"title": "Misc", "source": "ligolo-ng", "source_label": "Ligolo-ng", "path": "Misc", "html": "<h1 id=\"misc-faq\">Misc / FAQ</h1>\n<h2 id=\"demo\">Demo</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/nicocha30/ligolo-ng/assets/31402213/3070bb7c-0b0d-4c77-9181-cff74fb2f0ba\">Ligolo-ng-demo.webm</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"does-it-require-administratorroot-access\">Does it require Administrator/root access ?</h2>\n<p>On the <em>agent</em> side, no! Everything can be performed without administrative access.</p>\n<p>However, on your <em>relay/proxy</em> server, you need to be able to create a <em>tun</em> interface.</p>\n<h2 id=\"supported-protocolspackets\">Supported protocols/packets</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>TCP</li>\n<li>UDP</li>\n<li>ICMP (echo requests)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"performance\">Performance</h2>\n<p>You can easily hit more than 100 Mbits/sec. Here is a test using <code>iperf</code> from a 200Mbits/s server to a 200Mbits/s connection.\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>$<span class=\"w\"> </span>iperf3<span class=\"w\"> </span>-c<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;TARGET&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">24483</span>\nConnecting<span class=\"w\"> </span>to<span class=\"w\"> </span>host<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.0.1,<span class=\"w\"> </span>port<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">24483</span>\n<span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"m\">5</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">local</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.0.224<span class=\"w\"> </span>port<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">50654</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>connected<span class=\"w\"> </span>to<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">10</span>.10.0.1<span class=\"w\"> </span>port<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">24483</span>\n<span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>ID<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"